{
  "texts": [
    "First, data cleaning was applied to make the image data ready for AI-based analysis.",
    "In the second step, the data was preprocessed, models (networks) were trained, and the results were analyzed.",
    "Before training, the blood samples were preprocessed by background correction; no postprocessing was used for the urine samples.",
    "We developed three CNN-based models for BCa patient/control classification, one using the blood droplet images, and the other two using the urine droplet images prepared adding two different salt mixtures 28.",
    "Each model used the ResNet-18 network architecture with the modified last layers, which were one fully connected layer with 512 hidden units followed by rectified linear unit (ReLU) activation and dropout regularization and another fully connected layer with the softmax activation."
  ]
}